MASTERING CSS BASICS

1.UNDERSTANDING CSS

CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. It is a language used to style
and design web pages written in HTML.

CSS controls how elements look on a website, including:

Colors
Fonts
Spacing
Layout
Animations
Responsive design for mobile devices

Why “Cascading”?

The word cascading means styles can come from multiple places and are applied based on priority rules.


What CSS Works With

CSS is usually used together with:

HTML → structure/content
JavaScript → behavior/interactivity

Think of it like:

HTML = skeleton
CSS = clothing/design
JavaScript = movement/actions

CSS Syntax

CSS likhne ka basic structure:

selector {
  property: value;
}

Example:

h1 {
  color: blue;
  font-size: 40px;
}

2.ADDING CSS

Types of CSS
Inline CSS – inside an HTML tag
Internal CSS – inside a <style> tag
External CSS – stored in a separate .css file (most common)

CSS Add Karne Ke 3 Tarike
(1) Inline CSS

HTML tag ke andar.

<h1 style="color:red;">Hello</h1>
Problem
Code messy ho jata hai
Professional projects me avoid karte hain
(2) Internal CSS

HTML ke <style> tag me.

<head>
  <style>
    h1{
      color: blue;
    }
  </style>
</head>
(3) External CSS (Most Important)

Separate .css file banti hai.

HTML:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

style.css:

h1{
  color: green;
}

Professional projects me mostly ye use hota hai.

3.SELECTOR & PROPERTIES

Selectors decide karte hain kis element ko style dena hai.

(1) Element Selector
p{
  color:red;
}

Sab <p> tags red ho jayenge.

(2) Class Selector

HTML:

<div class="box"></div>

CSS:

.box{
  background: yellow;
}

Class . se start hoti hai.

(3) ID Selector

HTML:

<h1 id="title">Hello</h1>

CSS:

#title{
  color: purple;
}

ID # se start hoti hai.

